# Dynamic Recon

Research-style orchestration project for running Depth Anything 3 (DA3) and SAM 3 on a video, estimating depth and camera motion, tracking dynamic objects, and fusing both signals into static/dynamic 3D outputs.

## Repository layout

```text
.
├── configs/
├── dynamic_recon/
├── outputs/
├── scripts/
├── tests/
└── third_party/
```

The intended upstream submodules are:

- `third_party/depth_anything_3` -> `https://github.com/ByteDance-Seed/Depth-Anything-3.git`
- `third_party/sam3` -> `https://github.com/facebookresearch/sam3.git`

## Quick start

1. Initialize the repository if needed:

```bash
git init
./scripts/setup_submodules.sh
```

2. Create the dedicated conda environment:

```bash
./scripts/setup_env.sh
```

3. Authenticate to Hugging Face if required:

```bash
export HF_TOKEN=...
huggingface-cli login
```

4. Download checkpoints:

```bash
./scripts/download_checkpoints.sh
```

5. Run the demo:

```bash
python -m dynamic_recon.run \
  --video data/input.mp4 \
  --prompts "person,car,dog" \
  --output outputs/run01
```

## Dry run and smoke mode

Use dry-run to validate config and dependency wiring without inference:

```bash
python -m dynamic_recon.run --video data/input.mp4 --output outputs/run01 --dry-run
```

Use mock mode when the upstream packages or checkpoints are not installed yet:

```bash
python -m dynamic_recon.run \
  --video data/input.mp4 \
  --output outputs/run01 \
  --prompts "person,car" \
  --allow-mock-models
```

## Output structure

Typical output files:

```text
outputs/run01/
  depth/
    depth.npy
    conf.npy
    intrinsics.npy
    extrinsics.npy
    metadata.json
  frames/
  poses/
    cameras.txt
    images.txt
  sam3/
    masks/
    masks.npz
    prompts.json
    tracks.json
  masks_dynamic/
  masks_static/
  masks_uncertain/
  overlays/
  pointcloud_all_raw.ply
  pointcloud_static_raw.ply
  pointcloud_static_fused.ply
  pointcloud_dynamic_fused.ply
  summary.json
  visualization.mp4
```

## Reproducibility notes

- `scripts/setup_env.sh` attempts a single shared Python 3.12 environment first.
- If shared installation fails because DA3 and SAM3 diverge, use `scripts/setup_env_da3.sh` and `scripts/setup_env_sam3.sh` and run wrappers in subprocess mode.
- Checkpoints are stored outside git and should never be committed.

## Known limitations

- DA3 poses may drift on highly dynamic or texture-poor videos.
- SAM 3 tracks depend on prompt quality and checkpoint availability.
- 3D dynamic classification is sensitive to pose/depth noise and occlusions.
- The first version is research-grade, not production-grade.
